node.text:
With Halloween weekend approaching, we asked some campus representatives to share some valuable advice on how to keep you and your peers safe this spooky season! 👻 The impact of COVID-19 means our Chico State community will have to celebrate Halloween a little differently this year. We encourage Wildcats to rise to the challenge and avoid large gatherings. Instead, be creative with how you celebrate by gathering virtually or with roommates. Butte County has made improving progress in reopening and limiting the spread of COVID-19, and it's critical to do your part so we don't backtrack on the progress our community has already made. 

🚨 If you see something inappropriate or dangerous, speak up and call 911. 🚨 If you notice a large gathering, you can contact University Police through their anonymous tip form. It's important to keep our Wildcat family safe and take care of each other. The greatest thing we can do in this time is continuing to make progress on the pandemic and turning towards a more normal life. Stay safe this Halloween, Wildcats! 🎃 🐾

node.text:
Wildcat Welcome is here! Are you ready? Come out tomorrow night for our ✨Sunset Social✨ and enjoy food, games, music, and more! Activities are from 5 -8 p.m. between Glenn Hall and the new Science Building.

And don't miss out on 2 more nights of fun! 🌮Tunes & Tacos is this Friday from 6-8 p.m. on Glenn Lawn. You can look forward to tacos from Tacos Super Tonaya, music from local artist Kyle Williams and more.

End the weekend with a 🌙Moonlight Movie on Saturday, our first of many this fall. Boba and popcorn will be available at 7:30 and free blankets for the first 100 Wildcats. Movie starts at 8:30 on Glenn Lawn.

For more Wildcat Welcome events, check the full calendar at http://csuchico.edu/wildcatwelcome

📸🍿: @jasonhalley_csu

🍑It's peach season! The College of Agriculture's annual U-Pick Peaches event begins today, 8 a.m. to noon at the University Farm. Come on down to the farm and pick your own delicious Fey Elberta peaches for just $2 per pound! 

Sales will continue on August 10 and 11 or until supplies run out. Call the Peach Hotline to check availability at 530-898-4989.
